Great/Terrible visited twice (Saturday and Sunday after Colts game); completely two different experiences. Saturday: Slow day not overly crowded. Order wings and fries; then more wings which took about 20 mins but was worth it. Wings were amazing, fresh hot not overly drenched in sauce. So good that i even order a burger which was great. Chef was James, amazing food.  Sunday: Given my experience the day before i return here after the Colts game for more wings. It was crowded but expected; took about 10 mins to get seated. I proceed to order large portion of wings and request that James prepare it (as there was another chef) and that he can take his time; no rush.  Waitress told me not a problem. Food came out in 5 mins, completely drenched in sauce. Once I bit into the wings; cold. I sent them back to redo and notice the other chef making a scene. They basically microwaved the wings and sent the same drenched wings back. At that point i left. I was offer a 30% discount but in reality it was 3% when i got my bill. When I made my waitress aware it was 3% she stood firmly and said it was no that 30%; was not in mood of going back and forth.  I would not advise to come here during game day or any busy day as service and food is terrible. If James is not preparing your meal turn around and leave!

The food is bloody awful. I was forced to come here because staying at nearby Comfort Suites, also an extra royal dump of a place. Quick walk to this place. Cheese pizza was frozen store bought and microwaved. Mac and cheese store bought and not even decently heated through in microwave. God forbid if I ever have misfortune of staying on this side of town again. Frozen tv dinner would have been far far better. Forget the food just have a drink.

Wow... what can I say, with only 2 tables in the place for lunch it took 45 minutes for food but not the end of the world since we were not in a hurry. As for the food, I had wings, which were a tad overcooked, great if you are into that but not me. Average salads and dull beer selection on tap with a decent selection in the beer fridge.  This place would have been your normal 3 star rating right up to the point where one of the kiddies tripped on an exposed light cord and toppled a beer sign sitting carelessly on a window ledge. Crash down came the sign, thankfully no injured little one when the glass shattered.  We were feeling bad, trying to help clean up... right up to the point where the owner said "don't worry I don't blame the kids, but the parents".   Maybe one of the worst comments ever, but after reading the reviews here on yelp it's par for the course.  We left in two seconds flat never to return, wish I could give mgmt Zero Stars.

Every year, Basey's unofficially hosts ALL of Drum Corps International at their establishment after finals night. They are incredibly welcoming and have made it a tradition to celebrate a successful summer of hard work at Basey's. I recommend it to everyone going to Indy just for their hospitality alone.

I came in with my gf on her birthday. The waitress told us they had Matilda on tap for $5. She gives us our beers and then tells us it is actually $8. Im not cheap but if you quote a price you should stick by it if you have already served it. But that wasn't the biggest deal in the world. During the meal the waitress doesn't come back and I am so thirsty. About this time the owner comes in and talks to us. He starts bragging about his food which was a turnoff. I don't need the owner of any establishment to tell me how good his food is I have taste buds for that. When he finds out through conversation it is my GF's birthday he says, "oh, I would buy you a drink but you are drinking a pepsi". We weren't looking for anything free at all but that seemed very cheap to me. As far as the food. It was good. It wasn't great. We had been to O'Reillys pub a few days prior to this and it was much more rememberable.  I don't doubt they are nice people. I can only share what happened when we went there.
Its hard to give a decent review of this place. When you walk in it looks like a typical bar. The reason for 3 stars was it smelled like old fry oil. The bartender was nice and the food was OK.

Great spot to go for great burgers, especially if you're staying at the Holiday Inn Express or you're at Lucas Oil Stadium. Nice staff, clean establishment. Food taste fresh and vibrant with nice flavors.
Great food! I had the fish (battered) sandwich. My other half ordered the Basey's dble cheese burger. Both sandwiches were huge!!! VERY YUMMY!

I was a bit deterred when I read the "Kevin F" comment, but I had a word with the hotel staff and they suggested it...so I gave it a shot. It was quiet, probably because it was during the work week and not during football season; this place is in the shadow of Lucas Oil stadium (think Colts football). Now, I only ate one dish but it was so good that I had to come back another day to have it again before I flew out; its the fried pork tenderloin sandwich with the seasoned fries. The service was good, the bartenders friendly, and the beer cold. This is not a suit-and-tie resturant but it is a great place for food.  -MiC
